g.title: /** * JSDoc typedefs and mapping notes for child popup (Tabulator / ChannelList) main chartManager * * @typedef {Object} ChildMessagePayload * @property {string} [channelID] - channel unique id (if message uses id-based updates) * @property {number|string} [newValue] - new value (e.g. color, numeric value) * @property {number|string} [start] - start index or timestamp for a channel * @property {number|string} [duration] - duration (number of samples or ms depending on mapping) * @property {Object} [row] - Tabulator row object when using row-based updates * * @typedef {Object} ChildToParentMessage * @property {string} source - e.g. 'ChildWindow' * @property {string} type - one of the CALLBACK_TYPE constants (e.g. 'CALLBACK_TYPE.START', 'CALLBACK_TYPE.DURATION') * @property {ChildMessagePayload} payload - payload object described above * * Mapping (high-level) * - Tabulator / ChannelList (child popup) sends a message via window.postMessage to the parent with * { source: 'ChildWindow', type: CALLBACK_TYPE.START, payload: { channelID, start } } * - `src/main.js` receives the message in the global message handler and translates it to a state update * using helpers like `updateChannelFieldByID` or `updateChannelFieldByIndex`. This mutates `channelState`. * - `src/components/chartManager.js` subscribes to `channelState` changes (using * `channelState.subscribeProperty('start')` and `channelState.subscribeProperty('duration')`). * The subscriber resolves sample-index time via `resolveTimeRange(...)` and then applies the x-axis * scale to the uPlot instance (via `applyScale` / `chart.setScale('x', {min, max})`). * * Example flow (concrete): * - Child: window.postMessage({ source: 'ChildWindow', type: 'CALLBACK_TYPE.START', payload: { channelID: 'ch-12', start: 100 } }, '*') * - main.js: receives message, calls updateChannelFieldByID('ch-12', 'start', 100) -> channelState updated * - chartManager: channelState subscriber runs, maps sample index 100 -> timestamp using dataState, then * calls chart.setScale('x', { min: t0, max: t0 + duration }) (via robust applyScale helper) * * Notes: * - `start` and `duration` in channelState may be sample indices or already-converted times; the * `resolveTimeRange` helper centralizes conversion logic. Documenting the shape here helps keep * message producers (Tabulator) and consumers (chartManager) in sync. */ newValue: value
